Vicon Industries Inc. said Japan's Chugai Boyeki Co. raised its stake in the maker of closed-circuit video systems to 14.9% from 11.7%. 

Vicon said Chugai, a trading company, acquired 100,000 Vicon shares at $9.50 apiece. 

At the same time, Vicon said it granted Chugai the exclusive right to sell Vicon's video products, which are used in security and control applications, in Japan. 

In the nine months ended June 30, Vicon had a loss of $512,000, or 19 cents a share, on sales of $32.6 million. 

